	abstract = {Migrating birds affected by climate change in the Arctic may have lower survival chances in their tropical habitats
          , 
            
              Humans have long used animals as sentinels for threats to their own well-being. Canaries in coal mines are a classic example. On a global scale, studies of birds were key to detecting environmental problems caused by the excessive use of pesticides (
              
